HOUSE BILL 1599
M1, M2 6lr3603
CF SB 558
By: Delegates Jacobs, Anderson, Arentz, Beauchamp, Ghrist, Hartman,
Hutchinson, and Sample–Hughes Sample–Hughes, Allen, Behler, Boyce,
Healey, Holmes, Lewis, J. Long, T. Morgan, Odom, Stein, and Ziegler
Introduced and read first time: February 16, 2026
Assigned to: Rules and Executive Nominations
Re–referred to: Environment and Transportation, February 26, 2026
Committee Report: Favorable with amendments
House action: Adopted
Read second time: March 25, 2026
CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Chesapeake Bay Enhancement Program – Established
3 Chesapeake Bay – Enhancement Program and Maryland Seafood Industry
4 Financial Assistance Fund – Established
5 FOR the purpose of establishing the Chesapeake Bay Enhancement Program to provide
6 funding for certain oyster propagation and replenishment projects that mitigate the
7 effects on the State’s oyster population of certain transportation projects on the
8 State’s oyster population; establishing the Maryland Seafood Industry Financial
9 Assistance Fund to provide financial assistance to certain commercial watermen and
10 small businesses; prohibiting the Department of Natural Resources from making
11 certain approvals for tidal fish licenses or authorizations of certain borrowers; and
12 generally relating to the Chesapeake Bay Enhancement Program and Maryland
13 Seafood Industry Financial Assistance Fund.
14 BY adding to
15 Article – Natural Resources
16 Section 4–1020.1
17 Annotated Code of Maryland
18 (2023 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
19 BY adding to
20 Article – Economic Development
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from existing law.
Underlining indicates amendments to bill.
Strike out indicates matter stricken from the bill by amendment or deleted from the law by
amendment. *hb1599*

2 HOUSE BILL 1599
1 Section 10–526.1 and 10–526.2
2 Annotated Code of Maryland
3 (2024 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
4 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
5 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
6 Article – Natural Resources
7 4–1020.1.
8 (A) IN THIS SECTION, “PROGRAM” MEANS THE CHESAPEAKE BAY
9 ENHANCEMENT PROGRAM.
10 (B) THERE IS A CHESAPEAKE BAY ENHANCEMENT PROGRAM IN THE
11 DEPARTMENT.
12 (C) THE PURPOSE OF THE PROGRAM IS TO PROVIDE FUNDING FOR OYSTER
13 PROPAGATION AND REPLENISHMENT PROJECTS THAT MITIGATE THE EFFECTS ON
14 THE STATE’S OYSTER POPULATION OF TRANSPORTATION PROJECTS THAT
15 MAINTAIN OR EXPAND THE HELEN DELICH BENTLEY PORT OF BALTIMORE,
16 INCLUDING:
17 (1) DREDGING;
18 (2) THE CONSTRUCTION OR MAINTENANCE OF:
19 (I) PIERS;
20 (II) BRIDGES; OR
21 (III) SHIPPING CHANNELS; AND
22 (3) CONSTRUCTION AT THE HELEN DELICH BENTLEY PORT OF
23 BALTIMORE OF TRANSPORTATION PROJECTS ON THE STATE’S OYSTER
24 POPULATION.
25 (D) FOR FISCAL YEAR 2028 AND EACH FISCAL YEAR THEREAFTER, THE
26 GOVERNOR SHALL INCLUDE IN THE ANNUAL BUDGET BILL AN APPROPRIATION OF
27 $2,000,000 TO THE PROGRAM FROM THE TRANSPORTATION TRUST FUND UNDER §
28 3–216 OF THE TRANSPORTATION ARTICLE THE DEPARTMENT SHALL USE FUNDING
29 UNDER THE PROGRAM TO SUPPORT OYSTER PROPAGATION AND REPLENISHMENT
30 AND PROGRAM MANAGEMENT.

HOUSE BILL 1599 3
1 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That the Laws of Maryland read
2 as follows:
3 Article – Economic Development
4 10–526.1.
5 (A) IN THIS SECTION, “FUND” MEANS THE MARYLAND SEAFOOD INDUSTRY
6 FINANCIAL ASSISTANCE FUND.
7 (B) THERE IS A MARYLAND SEAFOOD INDUSTRY FINANCIAL ASSISTANCE
8 FUND.
9 (C) THE PURPOSE OF THE FUND IS TO PROVIDE FINANCIAL ASSISTANCE,
10 INCLUDING LOANS, TO COMMERCIAL WATERMEN AND SMALL BUSINESSES IN THE
11 SEAFOOD INDUSTRY.
12 (D) THE CORPORATION SHALL ADMINISTER THE FUND.
13 (E) THE FUND CONSISTS OF:
14 (1) MONEY APPROPRIATED IN THE STATE BUDGET TO THE FUND;
15 (2) LOAN PRINCIPAL REPAYMENTS RELATED TO THE FINANCIAL
16 ASSISTANCE UNDER THIS SECTION;
17 (3) MONEY MADE AVAILABLE FROM THE FEDERAL, STATE, OR LOCAL
18 GOVERNMENT; AND
19 (4) ANY OTHER MONEY FROM ANY OTHER SOURCE ACCEPTED FOR
20 THE BENEFIT OF THE FUND.
21 (F) THE FUND MAY BE USED ONLY FOR:
22 (1) FINANCIAL ASSISTANCE, INCLUDING LOANS; AND
23 (2) THE COSTS OF THE CORPORATION TO ADMINISTER THIS SECTION.
24 (G) FOR FINANCIAL ASSISTANCE, INCLUDING LOANS, PROVIDED UNDER
25 THIS SECTION, THE CORPORATION SHALL DETERMINE THE FOLLOWING:
26 (1) THE APPLICATION AND AWARD PROCESS;
27 (2) ELIGIBILITY CRITERIA;

4 HOUSE BILL 1599
1 (3) THE AMOUNT OF THE FINANCIAL ASSISTANCE, INCLUDING LOANS,
2 FOR EACH APPLICANT;
3 (4) THE TERMS AND CONDITIONS OF FINANCIAL ASSISTANCE,
4 INCLUDING LOANS;
5 (5) THE AMOUNT OF LOAN FORGIVENESS THAT THE CORPORATION
6 MAY PROVIDE FOR LOAN REPAYMENT PERFORMANCE; AND
7 (6) ANY OTHER PROVISIONS NECESSARY TO CARRY OUT THIS
8 SECTION.
9 10–526.2.
10 (A) (1) IF A BORROWER WHO HOLDS A TIDAL FISH LICENSE UNDER §
11 4–701 OF THE NATURAL RESOURCES ARTICLE IS DELINQUENT IN THE REPAYMENT
12 OF A LOAN UNDER THIS SUBTITLE, THE CORPORATION SHALL NOTIFY THE
13 DEPARTMENT OF NATURAL RESOURCES.
14 (2) IF A BORROWER UNDER PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS SUBSECTION
15 BECOMES COMPLIANT WITH THE REPAYMENT OF A LOAN UNDER THIS SUBTITLE,
16 THE CORPORATION SHALL NOTIFY THE DEPARTMENT OF NATURAL RESOURCES.
17 (B) NOTWITHSTANDING § 4–701 OF THE NATURAL RESOURCES ARTICLE,
18 AFTER RECEIVING A NOTIFICATION UNDER SUBSECTION (A)(1) OF THIS SECTION
19 AND UNTIL RECEIVING A NOTIFICATION UNDER SUBSECTION (A)(2) OF THIS
20 SECTION, THE DEPARTMENT OF NATURAL RESOURCES MAY NOT APPROVE A
21 TRANSFER OF THE TIDAL FISH LICENSE OR AUTHORIZATION.
22 SECTION 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That:
23 (1) the Maryland Agricultural and Resource–Based Industry Development
24 Corporation may transfer up to $337,500 each from the Oyster Shucking House Loan
25 Program and the Watermen’s Microloan Program to the Maryland Seafood Industry
26 Financial Assistance Fund established under Section 2 of this Act to provide additional
27 financial assistance to commercial watermen and small businesses in the seafood industry;
28 and
29 (2) the Maryland Agricultural and Resource–Based Industry Development
30 Corporation shall repay any funds transferred from the Oyster Shucking House Loan
31 Program or the Watermen’s Microloan Program to the Maryland Seafood Industry
32 Financial Assistance Fund established under Section 2 of this Act on or before June 30,
33 2028.

HOUSE BILL 1599 5
1 SECTION 4. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That Sections 2 and 3 of this Act
2 shall take effect July 1, 2026.
3 SECTION 2. 5. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That, except as provided in
4 Section 4 of this Act, this Act shall take effect October 1, 2026.
Approved:
